## Quick start

```bash
make install
alembic upgrade head
make run
```

Open `http://localhost:8000/docs` for the auto-generated Swagger UI,
or `http://localhost:8000/openapi.json` for the raw contract.

## Testing & coverage

```bash
make test       # pytest + --cov-fail-under=80
```

Coverage threshold matches `COVERAGE_THRESHOLDS["python"]` in
`backend.software_simulator` — see the OmniSight X1 simulate-track docs
for why 80% is the floor.

## OpenAPI contract (N3 governance)

```bash
python scripts/dump_openapi.py          # regenerate openapi.json
python scripts/dump_openapi.py --check  # fail on drift
```

Wire `--check` into CI to gate API-breaking changes at PR time.

## Container & k8s

```bash
make docker
docker compose up -d

make helm       # helm lint + package
```

## X4 compliance gates

```bash
python -m backend.software_compliance --app-path .
```

The shipped `spdx.allowlist.json` denies GPL/AGPL by default. Adjust
the allowlist if a dependency needs a waiver — log the waiver in the
project's role skill.
